Question 1B: Spatial Regression (20 marks)

Shared with you are two files:

  1. “italy.shapefile”, a shapefile consisting geometries of the Italian regions along with the following attributes,

  1. REGION: name of the Italian region

  2. VAR_UNEMP: variation in unemployment

  3. VAR_RGDP: variation in real GDP

  1. “it.nb”, a GAL file to generate queen contiguity neighbours of the Italian regions.
library(sf); library(spdep); library(spatialreg)

Answer the following questions:

  1. (5 marks) Load the italy.shapefile and regress VAR_UNEMP on VAR_RGDP. (The inverse relationship between the variation in unemployment and variation in real GDP is known as Okun’s law in the economics literature.)

  1. Check for homoskedasticity and normality of the regression errors.
lmtest::bptest(OLS) # Do not reject H0: homoskedasticity
## 
##  studentized Breusch-Pagan test
## 
## data:  OLS
## BP = 0.022502, df = 1, p-value = 0.8808
tseries::jarque.bera.test(OLS$residuals) # Do not reject H0: normal

##  Jarque Bera Test

  1. (5 marks) Load the GAL file and create a neighbourhood connectivity plot on a map of Italy. Conduct Moran’s tests on the OLS residuals and the model variables to check whether spatial spill-over effects need to be considered in the model.
# nb

# Tests to detect spatial autocorrelation

# in OLS residuals
lm.morantest(OLS, it_lw) # Reject null of CSR
## 
##  Global Moran I for regression residuals
## 
## data:  
## model: lm(formula = VAR_UNEMP ~ VAR_RGDP, data = italy)
## weights: it_lw
## 
## Moran I statistic standard deviate = 2.8459, p-value = 0.002214
## alternative hypothesis: greater
## sample estimates:
## Observed Moran I      Expectation         Variance 
##       0.41745849      -0.06686060       0.02896088
moran.plot(OLS$residuals, it_lw, main="Moran Plot for OLS residuals")

# in other variables
moran.test(italy$VAR_UNEMP, it_lw) # Reject null of CSR

  1. (10 marks) Run the usual spatial regressions and conduct appropriate tests to identify the most suitable spatial regression model.
unemp_SAR = spautolm(formula = VAR_UNEMP ~ 1, data=italy, listw=it_lw)
unemp_SLM = lagsarlm(formula = VAR_UNEMP ~ VAR_RGDP, data=italy, listw=it_lw)
unemp_SEM = errorsarlm(formula = VAR_UNEMP ~ VAR_RGDP, data=italy, listw=it_lw)
unemp_SARAR = sacsarlm(formula = VAR_UNEMP ~ VAR_RGDP, data=italy, listw=it_lw)

# tests
lm.LMtests(OLS, listw=it_lw, test="all") # possible SLM
